snippet.textDisplay: Initially I was forwarding the rap part as it was spoiling the folk for me. But after listening to the entire track a couple of times, I finally get the point of the rap. Check the lyrics. The folk talks about draupadi and Sita and how women always faced their "tan's kattey". But the rap talks about an example of a  modern girl rising above everthing and surviving in this big bad world with head held high. Ram Sampath probably is focussing on showing woman power in his 'devi' themed episode.

snippet.textDisplay:
I see many people questioning the inclusion of Hard Kaur's rap here. Fair enough. This is a piece of art, and everyone is free to have their likes and dislikes.
I think the rap is fab! I have never liked rap music. But her rap made me stop and listen to her. She is obviously talking about some deeply personal and disturbing issues of her life- like losing her father in the 84' riots. It all moved me. Besides, her rap totally went with the badass nature of the song anyways!
